      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEPTIMUS (6) has attracted solid market support at his past 2 outings without producing the expected result, but this appears a far more suitable contest. He has changed stables with a probable jumping career ahead of him, and maybe the change of scenery can help him bounce back to his best. DIGARI (7) showed promise with a placing when resuming before failing to reproduce that effort at Murray Bridge last start in a better field off a wide gate. This is easier, and he should be right in the mix. LISA LASS (8) has found stronger company a little too testing at her past two starts, but this drop in grade gives her an excellent chance to bounce back at some each-way value. SIDE PIECE (10) needs it heavy, and with conditions to suit, he is capable of a top 3 finish in this sort of field.",
